Cassia has a degree in Ecology and Environmental Analysis (Universidade Federal de Goi√°s, 2016) and a master's degree in Biology of Continental Aquatic Environments (FURG, 2018). She is currently a PhD student in Biology of Continental Aquatic Environments and is working with ecosystem services in the Pampa biome, evaluating how the conversion of natural grasslands to monocultures affects the supply of services.
